3
00:01:00,330 --> 00:01:03,360
   

4
00:01:03,360 --> 00:01:06,000
   

5
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:09,080
   

6
00:01:10,620 --> 00:01:15,040
That place is in Wuzhu Village, Hepu, in the Gui Region.

7
00:01:15,040 --> 00:01:17,340
It's my hometown.

8
00:01:17,340 --> 00:01:19,140
 For generations, villagers have fished for pearls. 

9
00:01:19,140 --> 00:01:21,640
 They dive for clams and get pearls. 

10
00:01:21,640 --> 00:01:23,700
 In our ancestral hall is the God of Water. 

11
00:01:23,700 --> 00:01:27,420
 On its roof ridge, there are animals of Immortals Leading the Way. 

12
00:01:27,420 --> 00:01:30,280
Actually, in Xiaoshang River, when I painted for the first time,

13
00:01:30,280 --> 00:01:33,260
I saw the vision from the shadow of water.

14
00:01:33,260 --> 00:01:36,420
But before I finished it, I didn't know what it was.

15
00:01:36,420 --> 00:01:38,960
I was too shocked to tell anyone about it.

16
00:01:38,960 --> 00:01:44,600
And I didn't know you guys would see the same vision one after another.

17
00:01:45,300 --> 00:01:50,080
The shadow of water is one thing while the vision is another.

18
00:01:50,080 --> 00:01:55,360
How can you be sure the exact thing in your village is what we are after?

19
00:01:55,360 --> 00:01:58,560
Because I smashed the last animal.

20
00:01:58,560 --> 00:02:02,060
It was my hands that took it away.

21
00:02:02,060 --> 00:02:05,680
- Why didn't you tell us? 
 - Because I hate that place!

22
00:02:12,140 --> 00:02:14,100
Wuzhu Village.

23
00:02:14,100 --> 00:02:15,700
Glad we have an address now.

24
00:02:15,700 --> 00:02:16,980
I'll check the map.

25
00:02:16,980 --> 00:02:18,820
It's a small village.

26
00:02:18,820 --> 00:02:20,840
You can't find it on the map.

27
00:02:25,860 --> 00:02:28,260
I can take you there.

28
00:02:28,260 --> 00:02:29,600
But there is a condition.

29
00:02:29,600 --> 00:02:31,340
Tell me.

30
00:02:36,660 --> 00:02:38,640
Keep me safe.

31
00:02:40,700 --> 00:02:42,160
Deal.

32
00:03:20,720 --> 00:03:22,532
   

33
00:03:22,532 --> 00:03:24,760
   

34
00:03:26,700 --> 00:03:28,540
The cool bartender isn't here.

35
00:03:28,540 --> 00:03:29,940
He isn't here.

36
00:03:29,940 --> 00:03:31,920
I'll serve you.

37
00:03:31,920 --> 00:03:33,712
Sorry about that.

38
00:03:33,712 --> 00:03:36,780
- Fine, then. 
 - Oh, poor me.

39
00:03:37,380 --> 00:03:40,380
Xiao Luo took away Thirteen-Thousand.

40
00:03:40,380 --> 00:03:42,120
The workload isn't a problem.

41
00:03:42,120 --> 00:03:44,240
I just feel way too lonely.

42
00:03:44,240 --> 00:03:46,240
I'm a party person, after all.

43
00:03:46,240 --> 00:03:49,140
Luckily, Master is here with me.

44
00:03:49,140 --> 00:03:51,860
Or how could I live?

45
00:03:51,860 --> 00:03:53,720
I even feel life is meaningless.

46
00:03:53,720 --> 00:03:56,200
Life is actually meaningless.

47
00:03:57,680 --> 00:03:59,460
What would you like, Sir?

48
00:03:59,460 --> 00:04:01,060
I've got this.

49
00:04:02,760 --> 00:04:04,660
You can sit for a while.

50
00:04:04,660 --> 00:04:07,880
But this is an area for paid food.

51
00:04:07,880 --> 00:04:09,000
You can use this.

52
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:11,360
Is Mu Dai here?

53
00:04:11,360 --> 00:04:13,180
You know her?

54
00:04:13,820 --> 00:04:15,960
Tell her her senior is here.

55
00:04:15,960 --> 00:04:17,480
Who?

56
00:04:17,480 --> 00:04:21,880
You... You... look fine.

57
00:04:21,880 --> 00:04:25,020
My master punished him severely for that.

58
00:04:25,020 --> 00:04:26,920
 He's still recovering. His arms and legs are broken. 

59
00:04:26,920 --> 00:04:28,860
Your limbs have recovered?

60
00:04:28,860 --> 00:04:31,200
You look intact.

61
00:04:31,200 --> 00:04:32,580
What did she tell you?

62
00:04:32,580 --> 00:04:33,860
No, no.

63
00:04:33,860 --> 00:04:35,580
- Nothing. I just... 
 - Senior.

64
00:04:35,580 --> 00:04:38,180
You've an able body.

65
00:04:39,640 --> 00:04:40,760
Oh, gosh.

66
00:04:40,760 --> 00:04:42,640
When did you come?

67
00:04:42,640 --> 00:04:44,040
Get in there.

68
00:04:44,040 --> 00:04:46,560
You have a new hairstyle.

69
00:04:46,560 --> 00:04:48,040
I hate washing my hair.

70
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:51,920
Didn't you ask me to get you a job?

71
00:04:51,920 --> 00:04:53,580
- You got one? 
 - Yes.

72
00:04:53,580 --> 00:04:56,040
Go with me for an interview. Come on.

73
00:04:56,040 --> 00:04:58,600
- Where are we going? 
 - Huacheng.

74
00:04:58,600 --> 00:05:01,420
Huacheng? I need to get packed.

75
00:05:01,420 --> 00:05:02,600
No need.

76
00:05:02,600 --> 00:05:04,480
It's just 30 kilometers away. You'll be back soon.

77
00:05:04,480 --> 00:05:06,460
- You're right. 
 - Let's go.

78
00:05:07,040 --> 00:05:10,420
Tell Uncle Zhang I'm leaving with my senior.

79
00:05:10,420 --> 00:05:12,280
- What's your name? 
 - Cao.

80
00:05:12,280 --> 00:05:13,920
Xiao Cao.

81
00:05:14,920 --> 00:05:16,740
Thanks for taking care of Mu Dai.

82
00:05:16,740 --> 00:05:18,280
Life is meaningful in some ways.

83
00:05:18,280 --> 00:05:20,640
Yes, whatever you say.

84
00:05:20,640 --> 00:05:22,280
Go get my purse.

85
00:05:22,280 --> 00:05:23,480
Hurry. The train is leaving.

86
00:05:23,480 --> 00:05:26,360
Be right there. Hurry.

87
00:05:26,360 --> 00:05:28,740
- Bye- bye. 
 - I want to talk to him.

88
00:05:30,640 --> 00:05:33,820
Such a medical miracle!

89
00:05:33,820 --> 00:05:36,420
   

90
00:05:36,420 --> 00:05:38,640
Fancy house, indeed.

91
00:05:38,640 --> 00:05:40,420
A fancy house doesn't mean anything.

92
00:05:40,420 --> 00:05:42,840
All are made of clay bricks.

93
00:05:43,440 --> 00:05:44,880
Senior.

94
00:05:44,880 --> 00:05:46,300
Can I really be a bodyguard?

95
00:05:46,300 --> 00:05:49,520
Of course. You're my junior. You can do anything.

96
00:05:49,520 --> 00:05:52,320
Then... What should I do in the interview?

97
00:05:52,320 --> 00:05:55,440
Nothing. Just be yourself.

98
00:05:55,440 --> 00:05:57,560
Don't put on an act.

99
00:05:57,560 --> 00:05:59,960
They'll test you. You'll test them, too.

100
00:05:59,960 --> 00:06:01,760
If you feel upset, leave immediately.

101
00:06:01,760 --> 00:06:03,320
Don't hesitate.

102
00:06:03,320 --> 00:06:07,960
And remember. In your life, you must respect yourself.

103
00:06:07,960 --> 00:06:09,200
It makes sense.

104
00:06:09,200 --> 00:06:11,000
There you go.

105
00:06:15,120 --> 00:06:17,160
Old Yan, we're here.

106
00:06:18,840 --> 00:06:20,920
A minute, please.

107
00:06:20,920 --> 00:06:22,500
Here, Junior.

108
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:26,980
Remember. Don't put on an act.

109
00:06:27,640 --> 00:06:29,660
- Hello. 
  - Mu Dai, huh? 

110
00:06:29,660 --> 00:06:31,880
 See the stone table in front of you? 

111
00:06:31,880 --> 00:06:33,540
Yes.

112
00:06:38,040 --> 00:06:41,160
 There are words on it. Read them out. 

113
00:06:41,160 --> 00:06:45,080
"Gems bath in the moonlight."

114
00:06:45,080 --> 00:06:47,280
"And soil can't obscure them."

115
00:07:09,360 --> 00:07:11,420
Well done!

116
00:07:18,780 --> 00:07:22,580
Junior, I've told you many times to be gentle.

117
00:07:22,580 --> 00:07:24,800
What if you choke her?

118
00:07:27,860 --> 00:07:29,540
Hello.

119
00:07:31,620 --> 00:07:32,947
Nice to meet you.

120
00:07:32,947 --> 00:07:36,760
Someone recommended your clan.

121
00:07:36,760 --> 00:07:39,860
Hong Sha has never traveled alone.

122
00:07:39,860 --> 00:07:42,640
I want a female bodyguard to travel with her.

123
00:07:42,640 --> 00:07:44,760
Four or five days at most.

124
00:07:44,760 --> 00:07:47,820
This trip is all-inclusive.

125
00:07:47,820 --> 00:07:50,080
The pay is 20 thousand.

126
00:07:52,900 --> 00:07:54,420
It's the deposit.

127
00:07:54,420 --> 00:07:56,020
10 thousand.

128
00:07:57,160 --> 00:07:59,160
Senior.

129
00:08:01,760 --> 00:08:03,760
Quite a lot of money.

130
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:07,040
If necessary, I'll give you more.

131
00:08:07,040 --> 00:08:09,280
Where are we going then?

132
00:08:09,280 --> 00:08:10,780
What will we do?

133
00:08:10,780 --> 00:08:12,560
Hong Sha.

134
00:08:13,280 --> 00:08:15,200
Tell her about it.

135
00:08:20,760 --> 00:08:23,100
We're treasure hunters.

136
00:08:23,100 --> 00:08:24,920
Have you heard of it?

137
00:08:27,680 --> 00:08:31,140
Treasures refer to gems.

138
00:08:31,140 --> 00:08:33,160
They're priceless.

139
00:08:33,160 --> 00:08:36,400
Can we get them, then?

140
00:08:36,400 --> 00:08:38,680
Be patient, okay?

141
00:08:38,680 --> 00:08:42,200
Equipment is needed for the gems in the mine.

142
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:46,320
We don't do such hard jobs.

143
00:08:46,320 --> 00:08:50,486
Do you remember the remark on the table? What is it?

144
00:08:50,486 --> 00:08:51,931
"Soil can't obscure them."

145
00:08:51,931 --> 00:08:54,960
"Gems bath in the moonlight."

146
00:08:54,960 --> 00:08:57,120
"And soil can't obscure them."

147
00:08:57,120 --> 00:09:00,520
We only hunt this kind of gem.

148
00:09:00,520 --> 00:09:02,920
Why do you think you can get this kind of gem?

149
00:09:02,920 --> 00:09:05,360
People would get them first.

150
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:07,860
Such an ignorant amateur.

151
00:09:07,860 --> 00:09:12,020
Do you think gems will shine where they are?

152
00:09:12,020 --> 00:09:14,920
They're either encased in stone or wrapped in earth.

153
00:09:14,920 --> 00:09:17,760
They're invisible to ordinary guys.

154
00:09:18,640 --> 00:09:23,620
Special eyes are needed to detect their spreading light.

155
00:09:23,620 --> 00:09:25,420
Got it?

156
00:09:27,760 --> 00:09:29,840
We don't dig from the earth.

157
00:09:29,840 --> 00:09:32,760
We only dive in water or wells.

158
00:09:32,760 --> 00:09:35,520
In water, we get pears and jade.

159
00:09:35,520 --> 00:09:37,840
In wells, we get gems.

160
00:09:37,840 --> 00:09:39,760
According to ancient books,

161
00:09:40,561 --> 00:09:43,540
"If there are gems in a well, the air will look crystal."

162
00:09:43,540 --> 00:09:46,080
- "Pearls are in the deep..." 
 - Hong Sha.

163
00:09:46,080 --> 00:09:48,720
This is too elusive to be understood.

164
00:09:48,720 --> 00:09:50,700
Let me tell you.

165
00:09:52,720 --> 00:09:55,080
Treasure hunters like us

166
00:09:55,720 --> 00:09:59,720
need the eye training.

167
00:10:01,680 --> 00:10:06,920
We locate the treasures with our eyes.

168
00:10:06,920 --> 00:10:09,680
But it exhausts our eyes terribly.

169
00:10:09,680 --> 00:10:15,260
So, we end up half-blind for the rest of our lives.

170
00:10:17,980 --> 00:10:20,440
I have a son.

171
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:22,620
He's Hong Sha's uncle.

172
00:10:22,620 --> 00:10:26,080
Instead of using this skill, he uses his own way.

173
00:10:26,080 --> 00:10:28,960
Some days ago, he went to the Gui Region.

174
00:10:28,960 --> 00:10:32,200
For some treasures.

175
00:10:32,200 --> 00:10:36,120
The other day, when I called him, I couldn't get through.

176
00:10:36,120 --> 00:10:39,040
When I could get through, he didn't answer.

177
00:10:39,040 --> 00:10:40,680
I located him.

178
00:10:40,680 --> 00:10:42,400
He was in that region.

179
00:10:42,400 --> 00:10:44,560
I'm really worried.

180
00:10:44,560 --> 00:10:46,780
But I have trouble moving around.

181
00:10:46,780 --> 00:10:51,920
So, I want you to take Hong Sha there.

182
00:10:51,920 --> 00:10:53,600
Gui Region?

183
00:10:53,600 --> 00:10:55,440
Around the Plateau Lake?

184
00:10:55,440 --> 00:10:58,680
Can you tell me the exact location?

185
00:10:59,440 --> 00:11:02,580
Wuzhu Village, Hepu.

186
00:11:03,560 --> 00:11:05,740
 What a coincidence. 

187
00:11:08,080 --> 00:11:11,480
The tunnel is closed. Go another way.

188
00:11:12,120 --> 00:11:13,300
   

189
00:11:13,300 --> 00:11:16,500
 The tunnel is closed. Go another way. 

190
00:11:18,780 --> 00:11:22,980
Thirteen-Thousand, the tunnel isn't available.

191
00:11:22,980 --> 00:11:26,180
In such remote areas, the navigation often goes wrong.

192
00:11:26,180 --> 00:11:27,440
Trust me.

193
00:11:27,440 --> 00:11:31,080
Go through the tunnel, and Wuzhu Village is just a few miles away.

194
00:11:31,080 --> 00:11:33,120
I remember the route clearly.

195
00:11:53,960 --> 00:11:55,900
The navigation is accurate.

196
00:11:55,900 --> 00:11:57,720
That's impossible.

197
00:11:57,720 --> 00:12:00,280
Drive through the tunnel and we'll arrive.

198
00:12:00,280 --> 00:12:03,200
It'll take a whole day if we go another way.

199
00:12:04,680 --> 00:12:07,460
I don't know why the tunnel is closed.

200
00:12:21,220 --> 00:12:23,200
My luggage.

201
00:12:23,200 --> 00:12:26,360
I'm your bodyguard, not your personal assistant.

202
00:12:27,400 --> 00:12:29,040
Oh, right.

203
00:12:31,040 --> 00:12:33,800
When we're in Hepu, what vehicle will we take?

204
00:12:33,800 --> 00:12:35,360
Where will we live after our mission?

205
00:12:35,360 --> 00:12:38,105
Have you arranged it? Have you got a plan?

206
00:12:39,220 --> 00:12:41,825
Your grandpa said this trip would be all-inclusive.

207
00:12:41,825 --> 00:12:43,645
So, arrange everything.

208
00:13:04,680 --> 00:13:07,200
I invited you over for a dance. It was lively, indeed.

209
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:08,817
- It tastes great. 
 - Look at this.

210
00:13:08,817 --> 00:13:12,195
Madam. Have you heard of a Wuzhu Village nearby?

211
00:13:12,195 --> 00:13:15,240
Yes. You're going there?

212
00:13:15,240 --> 00:13:17,360
Before, you could go through the old tunnel.

213
00:13:17,360 --> 00:13:19,360
But it's closed now.

214
00:13:19,360 --> 00:13:20,740
You'll have to take a detour.

215
00:13:20,740 --> 00:13:24,040
You can go by train. It's available there.

216
00:13:24,040 --> 00:13:28,200
Do you know why the tunnel is closed?

217
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:31,600
Because no one is there. The village is empty.

218
00:13:31,600 --> 00:13:33,540
Empty?

219
00:13:37,400 --> 00:13:40,080
I've heard people in this village do pearl hunting.

220
00:13:40,080 --> 00:13:41,560
For generations.

221
00:13:41,560 --> 00:13:42,800
How come it is empty?

222
00:13:42,800 --> 00:13:44,400
It's true.

223
00:13:44,400 --> 00:13:45,920
No pearls are available.

224
00:13:45,920 --> 00:13:47,260
So, people moved away.

225
00:13:47,260 --> 00:13:48,920
No pearls?

226
00:13:48,920 --> 00:13:50,920
But I heard there were many clams in the lake.

227
00:13:50,920 --> 00:13:52,680
There should have been pearls.

228
00:13:52,680 --> 00:13:55,200
Dude, you have no idea.

229
00:13:55,200 --> 00:13:57,480
On one Mid-Autumn night,

230
00:13:57,480 --> 00:14:00,340
Clams Basking in the Moon actually happened.

231
00:14:00,340 --> 00:14:02,300
Clams were everywhere on the shore.

232
00:14:02,300 --> 00:14:06,720
But a naughty boy burned them with gasoline.

233
00:14:06,720 --> 00:14:09,240
What a terrible kid. So wicked.

234
00:14:09,240 --> 00:14:10,440
That's right.

235
00:14:10,440 --> 00:14:15,780
I've heard, since then, no pearls have been found here.

236
00:14:15,780 --> 00:14:19,180
According to the locals, they offended the God of Water and had their comeuppance.

237
00:14:19,180 --> 00:14:22,140
Well, I think everything has a soul.

238
00:14:22,140 --> 00:14:25,380
When the clams were burned, they would hate this place.

239
00:14:25,380 --> 00:14:26,734
So, they'd never come again.

240
00:14:26,734 --> 00:14:27,820
- Right? 
 - Maybe.

241
00:14:27,820 --> 00:14:30,160
Why are you going there? Nothing's left there.

242
00:14:30,160 --> 00:14:33,880
I've also heard that the village is haunted now.

243
00:14:33,880 --> 00:14:35,460
Really?

244
00:14:35,460 --> 00:14:36,540
You don't know?

245
00:14:36,540 --> 00:14:38,699
Hey, stop. Sounds creepy.

246
00:14:38,699 --> 00:14:39,980
- Let's drink. 
 - Okay.

247
00:14:39,980 --> 00:14:41,120
- Come on. 
 - Here.

248
00:14:41,120 --> 00:14:42,160
- No. 
 - Join us.

249
00:14:42,160 --> 00:14:43,900
I have allergies.

250
00:15:13,960 --> 00:15:15,620
Second Uncle.

251
00:15:20,740 --> 00:15:22,050
   

252
00:15:23,480 --> 00:15:25,600
Hey, Second Uncle.

253
00:15:25,600 --> 00:15:27,574
Hello?

254
00:15:27,574 --> 00:15:29,864
Hey, Second Uncle. Can you hear me?

255
00:15:29,864 --> 00:15:31,364
Hello?

256
00:15:41,680 --> 00:15:45,600
 Sorry, the subscriber you dialed cannot be connected. 

257
00:15:45,600 --> 00:15:46,880
 Please redial later. 

258
00:15:46,880 --> 00:15:51,140
 Sorry... 

259
00:15:59,080 --> 00:16:00,620
Mu Dai.

260
00:16:03,940 --> 00:16:05,600
Wake up.

261
00:16:05,600 --> 00:16:07,440
Wake up now.

262
00:16:07,440 --> 00:16:08,560
Wake up.

263
00:16:08,560 --> 00:16:10,160
What's wrong?

264
00:16:10,160 --> 00:16:11,300
Get up now.

265
00:16:11,300 --> 00:16:13,560
What happened?

266
00:16:13,560 --> 00:16:15,420
Something's wrong.

267
00:16:17,060 --> 00:16:18,932
 Sorry... 

268
00:16:18,932 --> 00:16:22,160
Why can't I get through to him?

269
00:16:22,160 --> 00:16:23,540
Your uncle was missing.

270
00:16:23,540 --> 00:16:25,980
But he called you just now. Isn't it great?

271
00:16:25,980 --> 00:16:28,320
Maybe his phone is dead.

272
00:16:28,320 --> 00:16:30,820
He'll call you after charging it.

273
00:16:30,820 --> 00:16:32,440
Come on, he answered.

274
00:16:32,440 --> 00:16:34,560
He just didn't say anything.

275
00:16:34,560 --> 00:16:35,860
Is he in trouble?

276
00:16:35,860 --> 00:16:39,280
Maybe he couldn't say anything because of the low battery.

277
00:16:39,960 --> 00:16:42,220
My dream was horrible.

278
00:16:42,220 --> 00:16:43,680
It felt so real.

279
00:16:43,680 --> 00:16:47,040
People say dreams aren't real.

280
00:16:47,040 --> 00:16:49,280
Stop worrying.

281
00:16:49,280 --> 00:16:50,680
Go back to sleep.

282
00:16:50,680 --> 00:16:52,560
I'm so tired.

283
00:16:52,560 --> 00:16:55,160
