354
00:23:44,920 --> 00:23:46,480
 Mom! 

355
00:23:48,440 --> 00:23:50,460
 Did you hear? 

356
00:23:50,460 --> 00:23:52,200
 He's yelling for help. 

357
00:23:52,200 --> 00:23:53,640
 He's hunting pearls. 

358
00:23:53,640 --> 00:23:55,440
 He can't pull so many pearls. 

359
00:23:55,440 --> 00:23:57,840
 - I need to go now. 
 - Mom, you can't go. 

360
00:23:57,840 --> 00:24:00,040
 The wind's blowing hard. Mom! Mom! 

361
00:24:00,040 --> 00:24:01,920
 Get out of my way! 

362
00:24:04,160 --> 00:24:05,720
 Mom! 

363
00:24:16,140 --> 00:24:19,580
 Mom! Mom! 

364
00:24:19,580 --> 00:24:23,220
 Mom! Don't go! 

365
00:24:23,220 --> 00:24:25,320
 Come back! 

366
00:24:31,760 --> 00:24:33,040
 - You can't go! 
 - Let me go! 

367
00:24:33,040 --> 00:24:34,360
 - You can't go. 
 - You can't go. 

368
00:24:34,360 --> 00:24:36,120
 Don't be silly. You'll get killed. 

369
00:24:36,120 --> 00:24:37,920
 You can't go. 

370
00:24:38,580 --> 00:24:41,200
 Chief, please save my mother. 

371
00:24:41,200 --> 00:24:44,640
 Such strong waves. How can I save her? 

372
00:24:44,640 --> 00:24:46,400
 Nobody can get down to save her! 

373
00:24:46,400 --> 00:24:49,780
 Or they will just die! 

374
00:24:49,780 --> 00:24:51,580
 You're a madwoman. 

375
00:24:51,580 --> 00:24:52,740
 - Mom! 
 - She's insane! 

376
00:24:52,740 --> 00:24:54,580
 Let me go! 

377
00:24:59,600 --> 00:25:01,920
 Let me go! 

378
00:25:06,960 --> 00:25:08,980
 Mom! 

379
00:25:11,400 --> 00:25:17,092
 That night, the wind blew strongly on the water. 

380
00:25:17,092 --> 00:25:18,952
 Nobody saved her. 

381
00:25:22,000 --> 00:25:24,620
The next morning,

382
00:25:25,405 --> 00:25:27,705
she couldn't be found.

383
00:25:31,160 --> 00:25:34,740
Do you think I was really unlucky?

384
00:25:36,740 --> 00:25:39,080
I thought so, anyway.

385
00:25:40,280 --> 00:25:43,040
During that time, I often sneaked into the ancestral hall.

386
00:25:43,040 --> 00:25:47,816
I asked the God of Water what I had done wrong

387
00:25:47,816 --> 00:25:50,180
or what my family had done wrong.

388
00:25:50,180 --> 00:25:53,040
 I asked how we offended him. 

389
00:25:54,073 --> 00:25:56,433
 But he didn't reply. 

390
00:26:07,320 --> 00:26:09,308
 Close the door. 

391
00:26:14,808 --> 00:26:21,040
 I got you guys here to talk about Jiang Zhao. 

392
00:26:22,440 --> 00:26:24,120
 He's a poor kid. 

393
00:26:24,120 --> 00:26:28,240
 He needs a lot of money for his school and marriage. 

394
00:26:28,240 --> 00:26:34,260
 Why don't we split the cost evenly? 

395
00:26:34,260 --> 00:26:38,060
 Okay. Whatever you say. 

396
00:26:38,060 --> 00:26:40,360
 That's fine with me. 

397
00:26:41,840 --> 00:26:46,040
 Jiang Liu, say something. 

398
00:26:46,040 --> 00:26:49,040
 Chief, this is unfair. 

399
00:26:49,040 --> 00:26:51,155
 You didn't save his father. Why do I have to pay? 

400
00:26:51,155 --> 00:26:54,040
 Nonsense. I didn't kill him. 

401
00:26:54,040 --> 00:26:56,160
 I didn't push him into the water. 

402
00:26:56,160 --> 00:26:59,820
 You were just beside him. Why didn't you save him? 

403
00:27:00,960 --> 00:27:02,160
 It was too chaotic. 

404
00:27:02,160 --> 00:27:04,800
 We might not manage to save him. 

405
00:27:04,800 --> 00:27:07,600
 Anyway, his death isn't in vain. 

406
00:27:07,600 --> 00:27:11,680
 At least, we own the lake now. 

407
00:27:11,680 --> 00:27:13,040
 Yeah. 

408
00:27:13,040 --> 00:27:15,640
 We lost a man and they were guilty. 

409
00:27:15,640 --> 00:27:17,660
 They were too ashamed to come. 

410
00:27:17,660 --> 00:27:19,280
 The authorities pitied us too. 

411
00:27:19,280 --> 00:27:21,907
 Then, this lake was given to us. 

412
00:27:21,907 --> 00:27:26,706
 So, Jiang Zhao's father is our hero. 

413
00:27:26,706 --> 00:27:31,127
 We should take care of Jiang Zhao and raise him. 

414
00:27:31,127 --> 00:27:35,281
 - Don't be stingy on such small expenses. 
 - Fine, then. 

415
00:27:35,281 --> 00:27:38,800
 - Clams are basking in the moon. 
 - Clams are basking in the moon. 

416
00:27:38,800 --> 00:27:40,040
 - Clams. 
 - In the moon. 

417
00:27:40,040 --> 00:27:41,220
 It's really happening. 

418
00:27:41,220 --> 00:27:42,910
 Let's take a look. 

419
00:27:42,910 --> 00:27:44,052
 - Let's go. 
 - Clams. 

420
00:27:44,052 --> 00:27:46,260
 - Move. 
 - Be quick, Chief. 

421
00:28:05,260 --> 00:28:07,800
 I'll screw this. 

422
00:28:21,800 --> 00:28:26,006
 Then, what is Clams Basking in the Moon? 

423
00:28:26,605 --> 00:28:28,845
Clams Basking in the Moon?

424
00:28:29,553 --> 00:28:32,634
That's just a ridiculous legend here.

425
00:28:32,634 --> 00:28:37,015
During the Mid-Autumn Festival, if the clams come onto the shore,

426
00:28:37,015 --> 00:28:40,757
open their shells and bask in the moon,

427
00:28:40,757 --> 00:28:45,119
there will be a great harvest of pearls for the next year.

428
00:28:45,119 --> 00:28:50,600
Enough moonshine can make the pearls bigger and rounder.

429
00:28:51,440 --> 00:28:53,060
But did they deserve the pearls?

430
00:28:53,060 --> 00:28:55,120
They watched my father die heartlessly.

431
00:28:55,120 --> 00:28:56,960
Do you think they deserved that?

432
00:28:56,960 --> 00:28:59,400
A great harvest?

433
00:29:05,760 --> 00:29:07,320
Then what happened?

434
00:29:07,320 --> 00:29:08,940
What happened?

435
00:29:09,840 --> 00:29:13,161
I took some diesel there and burned the clams.

436
00:29:13,161 --> 00:29:16,420
 I climbed onto the roof and smashed Hangshi. 

437
00:29:16,420 --> 00:29:18,822
 Then, I ran away. 

438
00:29:18,822 --> 00:29:22,102
After that, I never told anyone about this.

439
00:29:31,140 --> 00:29:32,860
Am I to blame?

440
00:29:37,265 --> 00:29:38,885
Thirteen-Thousand...

441
00:29:40,191 --> 00:29:44,540
what's gone is gone.

442
00:29:46,170 --> 00:29:48,170
What matters

443
00:29:49,680 --> 00:29:51,700
is to live a good life now.

444
00:29:53,537 --> 00:29:55,411
Yes.

445
00:29:55,411 --> 00:29:57,211
You're right.

446
00:29:58,375 --> 00:30:01,035
We're here to save Ping Ting.

447
00:30:03,051 --> 00:30:06,377
Tell me. Where are we going now?

448
00:30:06,377 --> 00:30:07,958
The ancestral hall.

449
00:30:07,958 --> 00:30:11,140
The corner of its roof appeared in the vision.

450
00:30:11,140 --> 00:30:12,400
We'll find a clue there.

451
00:30:12,400 --> 00:30:14,120
Here we are.

452
00:30:34,180 --> 00:30:37,660
Someone cleans this hall regularly, or it wouldn't be so clean.

453
00:30:37,660 --> 00:30:39,960
Yeah. I noticed that, too. 
    

